titute]] at the [[University of Cambridge]] since 1992, and Director of Germline and Epigenomics Research since 2013.<ref name=scopus>{{Scopus id}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gurdon.cam.ac.uk/research/surani|title=Azim Surani \u2014 The Gurdon Institute|website=Gurdon.cam.ac.uk|accessdate=29 August 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Azra Meadows]] OBE {{spaced ndash}} honorary lecturer in the Institute of Biomedical and Life Sciences at The [[University of Glasgow]]<ref name=queen>{{cite web|accessdate=21 February 2012 |title=Queen honours ZSL Council Members |date=14 June 2008 |publisher=ZSL.com |url=http://www.zsl.org/science/news/queen-honours-zsls-secretary,478,NS.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104205422/http://www.zsl.org/science/news/queen-honours-zsls-secretary%2C478%2CNS.html |archivedate= 4 January 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Delwar Hussain]] \u2013 writer, anthropologist and correspondent for ''[[The Guardian]]''. In 2013, his first book ''Boundaries Undermined: The Ruins of Progress on the Bangladesh-India Border'' was published.<ref name=\"spitalfieldslifehussain\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.spitalfieldslife.com/2013/07/22/delwar-hussain-writer-anthropologist/|title=Delwar Hussain, Writer & Anthropologist|work= |location= |publisher=Spitalfields Life|date=22 July 2013|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Dilwar Hussain]] {{spaced ndash}} research fellow at [[The Islamic Foundation]] in Leicester; co-authored the 2004 book ''British Muslims Between Assimilation and Segregation''; is on the Home Office's committee tackling radicalisation and extremism<ref name=\"independenthussain\">{{cite news |last=Hussain|first=Dilwar|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/commentators/dilwar-hussain-never-mind-what-we-are-against-what-are-we-for-308565.html|title=Dilwar Hussain: Never mind what we are against. What are we for?|location= London|newspaper=The Independent|date=28 August 2005|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Alfred