 Empire|OBE]] in 2002 for his work in the field of race and ethnic relations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sites.cardiff.ac.uk/islamukcentre/virtual-centre/public-lectures/2015-public-lectures/professor-humayun-ansari/|title=Professor Humayun Ansari|date=26 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Mohammed Ghanbari]]{{spaced ndash}} professor at the [[University of Essex]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://privatewww.essex.ac.uk/~ghan/|title=Home Page for Mohammed Ghanbari|first=Mohammed|last=Ghanbari|website=privatewww.essex.ac.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Mohammad Hashem Pesaran]]{{spaced ndash}}academic, economist, professor of economics at [[Cambridge University]], fellow of [[Trinity College, Cambridge]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.econ.cam.ac.uk/faculty/person.html?id=pesaran&group=faculty|title=Faculty of Economics - Academic Staff|website=www.econ.cam.ac.uk|date=2017-06-12}}</ref>\n* [[Mona Siddiqui]] \u2013 University of Edinburgh'Professor of Islamic Studies a Public Understanding; regular contributor to BBC Radio 4, ''The Times'', ''Scotsman'', ''The Guardian'', and ''The Herald''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gla.ac.uk/departments/theology/staff/monasiddiqui/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080915025531/http://www.gla.ac.uk/departments/theology/staff/monasiddiqui/|url-status=dead|archive-date=15 September 2008|title=Professor Mona Siddiqui|publisher=University of Glasgow|accessdate=15 July 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Mushtaq Khan (economist)|Mushtaq Khan]] \u2013 [[Heterodox economics|Heterodox economist]] and Professor of Economics at the [[SOAS, University of London|School of Oriental and African Studies]]. His work focuses on the economics of poor countries, including contributions to the field of institutional economics and South Asian development.<ref name=\"soas\">{{cite web|url=http://www.soas.ac.uk/staff/staff31246.php|title=Professor Mushtaq Khan|publisher=University of London|date= |accessdate=1 March 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Reza Banakar]] \u2013 professor of socio-legal studies at the [[Un