inance/financialcrisis/3484579/First-British-Asian-billionaires-defy-the-downturn.html |title=First British Asian billionaires defy the downturn |author= Jon Swaine |date= 19 November 2008|work= |publisher=Telegraph Media Group |accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n* Sir [[Anwar Pervez]] \u2013 Pakistan-born billionaire businessman;  6th richest Asian in Great Britain and the richest Muslim; founder of the [[Bestway|Bestway Group]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2002/jun/17/religion.immigrationpolicy |title=The winners |author=Paul Kelso |date= 17 June 2002|work= The Guardian |accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref> \n* [[Asim Siddiqui]] \u2013 chairman and a founding trustee of [[The City Circle]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/asimsiddiqui|title=Asim Siddiqui|website=the Guardian}}</ref>\n* [[Atique Choudhury]] \u2013 restaurateur;<ref>{{cite news |last=Seal|first=Martyn|url=https://www.theguardian.com/theguardian/2001/may/05/features.jobsmoney2|title=How an Indian collared the Thai business|location= London|work=The Guardian|date=5 May 2001|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref> his restaurant Yum Yum won Best Thai Restaurant in London at the 2012 Asian Curry Awards<ref name=\"asiancurryawards\">{{cite web|url=http://www.asiancurryawards.com/9_November_Asian_Curry_Awards_press_launch_release_FINAL.pdf |title=Restaurateur |publisher=Asian Curry Awards |date=9 November 2012 |accessdate=1 July 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121207012639/http://www.asiancurryawards.com/9_November_Asian_Curry_Awards_press_launch_release_FINAL.pdf |archivedate= 7 December 2012 }}</ref>\n* [[Bajloor Rashid]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] \u2013 businessman and former president of the Bangladesh Caterers Association<ref name=\"bbc2\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-kent-16367667|title=Bangladeshi restaurant boss Bajloor Rashid made MBE|location=Kent|work=[[BBC News]