nuary 2019}}\n* [[Jan Uddin]] {{spaced ndash}} actor best known for his roles as [[Jalil Iqbal]] in [[BBC]] soap opera ''[[EastEnders]]'' and Sweet Boy in the film ''[[Shank (2010 film)|Shank]]''<ref name=\"asiana\">{{cite news|url=http://www.asiana.tv/entertainment/jan-uddin|title=Boy of Bengal|publisher=Asiana|date=30 November 2010|accessdate=14 February 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120424140905/http://www.asiana.tv/entertainment/jan-uddin|archive-date=24 April 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Jay Shareef]] {{spaced ndash}} award-winning stand-up comedian,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.comedy.co.uk/fringe/2014/jay_islaam/ |title=Jay Islaam |location= |work=[[British Comedy Guide]]|date=1 August 2014|accessdate=25 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Lamy | first=Joel | url=http://www.peterboroughtoday.co.uk/what-s-on/latest-leisure-lifestyle/dream-comes-true-for-peterborough-comedy-award-winner-1-6227478 | title=Dream comes true for Peterborough comedy award-winner | location= | publisher=[[Peterborough Evening Telegraph]] | date=9 August 2014 | accessdate=18 February 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131201235/http://www.peterboroughtoday.co.uk/what-s-on/latest-leisure-lifestyle/dream-comes-true-for-peterborough-comedy-award-winner-1-6227478 | archive-date=31 January 2016 | url-status=dead }}</ref> [[Television presenter|broadcaster]]<ref>{{cite web | last=Habib | first=Adam | url=http://www.edgemagazine.org/britains-muslim-comedy-revolution.html | title=Britain's Muslim Comedy Revolution | location= | publisher=Edge Magazine | date=15 February 2016 | accessdate=18 February 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160225134143/http://www.edgemagazine.org/britains-muslim-comedy-revolution.html | archive-date=25 February 2016 | url-status=dead }}</ref> and journalist.<ref>{{cite web | last= | first= | url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/jay-islaam | title=Jay Islaam Guardian Articles | location=| work=[[The G