ing-the-norms-an-offbeat-talent-in-the-male-dominated-bhangra-music/ |title=Breaking the norms: An offbeat talent in the male-dominated bhangra music |work=The Express Tribune |accessdate=15 December 2012|date=2012-04-05 }}</ref>\n* [[Rita Ora]] {{spaced ndash}} singer{{citation needed|date=January 2019}}\n* [[Riz Ahmed]] {{spaced ndash}} actor who played Omar in the movie ''[[Four Lions]]'' and Changez in ''[[The Reluctant Fundamentalist]]''\n* [[Rowshanara Moni]] {{spaced ndash}} singer and actress<ref name=\"cyList\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.cylist.com/List/405491635/rowshanara-moni-nijhum-raat.html|title=Rowshanara Moni: Nijhum Raat|location= |work= |publisher=cyList|accessdate=25 September 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Ruhul Amin (film director)|Ruhul Amin]] {{spaced ndash}} film director; has made 13 films for the [[BBC]] and [[Channel 4]]; most of his works are documentaries and experimental dramas<ref>{{cite book |authorlink=Arif Ali (publisher)|last=Ali|first=Arif|title=Third World Impact|year=1988|publisher=Hansib Pub.|isbn=978-1-870518-04-8|pages=512, 80|url=https://books.google.com/?id=OV1nAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22rahul+amin%22+film&q=%22rahul+amin%22#search_anchor|accessdate=31 October 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Runa Islam]] {{spaced ndash}} film and photography visual artist, nominated for the [[2008 Turner Prize|Turner Prize 2008]]<ref name=\"newagebdIslam\">{{cite news|url=http://www.newagebd.com/2008/oct/10/oct10/xtra_inner4.html |title=British-Bangladeshis who have made a mark |work=New Age Xtra |date=10\u201316 October 2008 |accessdate=22 November 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081030124247/http://www.newagebd.com/2008/oct/10/oct10/xtra_inner4.html |archivedate=30 October 2008 }}</ref><ref name=\"runa\">{{cite news |last=Davies|first=Serena|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/art/3648626/A-cable-car-named-desire.html|title=A cable car named desire|location= London|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=10 December 