02074742/http://nftsfilm-tv.ac.uk/index.php?module=Film&action=Film&film_id=231|archive-date=2 January 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* [[State of Bengal|Saifullah 'Sam' Zaman]] {{spaced ndash}} DJ and producer associated with the [[Asian Underground]] movement, recording as \"State of Bengal\"<ref name=\"stateofbengal\">{{cite news|url=http://www.sixdegreesrecords.com/artists.php?artist=State_of_Bengal |title=Six Degrees Records \u2013 State of Bengal |accessdate=8 March 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070211085348/http://sixdegreesrecords.com/artists.php?artist=State_of_Bengal |archivedate=11 February 2007 }}</ref>\n* [[Sakina Samo]]{{spaced ndash}} award-winning actress, producer and director<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/705320/sakinas-pearls-of-wisdom|title=Sakina's pearls of wisdom|first=From|last=InpaperMagazine|date=24 March 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Sami Yusuf]]{{spaced ndash}} musician<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kwintessential.co.uk/articles/article/Iran/Sami-Yusuf/610|title=News - Kwintessential UK}}</ref>\n* [[Sanober Hussain]] {{spaced ndash}} British Pakistani; became the first UK [[Miss Pakistan World]] 2011\n* [[Selma Chalabi]] \u2013 radio producer and journalist for BBC Wales.  She was born in the [[United Kingdom]] to an [[Iraq]]i father and [[English people|English]] mother, and was raised in [[Winchester, England|Winchester]].<ref name=\"CMA\">{{cite web\n |url=http://awards.commedia.org.uk/awardwinners/selmachalabi.htm\n |title=Selma Chalabi\n |work=commedia.org.uk\n |publisher=Commedia Millennium Awards\n |accessdate=2009-07-17\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011042852/http://www.awards.commedia.org.uk/awardwinners/selmachalabi.htm\n |archive-date=11 October 2008\n |url-status=dead\n }}</ref><ref name=\"VVCA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.valleyandvale.co.uk/video/video_movies.htm |title=Land of my Father |publisher=Valley and Vale Community Arts |accessdate=2009-07-17 |url-status