esh]]; best known for his lyric \"[[Amar Bhaier Rokte Rangano]]\", which has become the main song commemorating the [[Bengali language movement|Language Movement]]\n* [[Adil Ray]] {{spaced ndash}} British radio and television presenter, for [[BBC Asian Network]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/asiannetwork/adilray/ |title=Adil Ray |author=BBC Asian network |website= |publisher=BBC |accessdate=15 July 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Adnan Nawaz]] {{spaced ndash}} news and sports presenter for the BBC World Service<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/talking_point/6387413.stm |title=My Cricket World Cup |author=BBC News |work= |publisher=BBC |accessdate=15 July 2011 |date=22 February 2007}}</ref>\n* [[Ajmal Masroor]] \u2013 television presenter, politician, imam,<ref name=\"guardianajmal\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2004/nov/30/islamandbritain22|title=Ajmal Masroor, 33|location= London|work=The Guardian|date=30 November 2004|accessdate=30 January 2009}}</ref> and [[Prospective parliamentary candidate|UK Parliamentary candidate]] for [[Bethnal Green and Bow (UK Parliament constituency)|Bethnal Green and Bow constituency]] representing [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] in the [[2010 United Kingdom general election|2010 general election]];<ref name=\"ajmallibdem\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://tower-hamlets-libdems.org.uk/en/article/2008/097184/ajmal-masroor-selected-as-ppc-for-bethnal-green-and-bow-parliamentary-constituency|title=Ajmal Masroor selected as PPC for Bethnal Green and Bow parliamentary constituency|work= |location= |publisher=[[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] (Tower Hamlets)|date=26 September 2008|accessdate=30 January 2009}}</ref> television presenter on political and Islamic programmes on [[Islam Channel]] and [[Channel S]]<ref name=\"guardianajmal2\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/ajmalmasroor|title=Ajmal Masroor profile|location= London|work=