.html|title=Maneer Mirza|website=Cricinfo}}</ref>\n* [[Moeen Ali]] {{spaced ndash}} English cricketer; right arm [[off break]] bowler and left-handed batsman currently playing for [[Worcestershire County Cricket Club|Worcestershire]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/story/259860.html |title=Moeen Ali |website= |publisher=ESPNC EMEA|accessdate=15 July 2011|date=2006-09-18 }}</ref>\n* [[Mohammad Akhtar]] {{spaced ndash}} Pakistani-born English cricketer; right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm [[off break]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/45/45561/List_A_Matches.html|title=The Home of CricketArchive|website=www.cricketarchive.com}}</ref>\n* [[Moneeb Iqbal]] {{spaced ndash}} Scottish cricketer; right-handed batsman and leg-break bowler<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/44/44900/44900.html|title=The Home of CricketArchive|website=cricketarchive.com}}</ref>\n* [[Nadeem Malik (cricketer)|Nadeem Malik]] \u2013 English cricketer; right-arm fast-medium [[seam bowling|seam bowler]] and right-handed lower-order batsman<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/15182583.stm|title=Leicestershire thrilled White, Boyce and Malik are staying|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=10 October 2011|date=5 October 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Nadeem Mohammed]]{{spaced ndash}} former English cricketer; right-handed batsman who played bowled right-arm [[Seam bowling|medium pace]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/7/7301/Minor_Counties_Championship_Matches.html|title=The Home of CricketArchive|website=www.cricketarchive.com}}</ref>\n* [[Nadeem Shahid]] \u2013 former English [[first-class cricket]]er who played for Essex and Surrey\n* [[Naheem Sajjad]] \u2013 Pakistani-born English cricketer, a right-handed batsman who bowls left-arm [[Fast bowling|fast-medium]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/9/9081/Minor_Counties_Championship_Matches.html|title=The Home 