 sign ex-Daggers captain |publisher=Sutton United F.C. |date=3 February 2012 |accessdate=3 February 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160512064011/http://www.suttonunited.net/news.php |archivedate=12 May 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Atif Bashir]] {{spaced ndash}} footballer with a ([[British Pakistanis|British Pakistani]] father and a Turkish ]] mother)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/picturegalleries/picturesoftheday/8608030/Pictures-of-the-day-30-June-2011.html?image=19|title=Pictures of the day |date= 30 June 2011|work= The Telegraph |accessdate=15 July 2011|location=London}}</ref>\n* [[Easah Suliman]] \u2013 footballer currently playing for [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]. Suliman has represented England at youth level; first player of Asian heritage to captain an England representative side, having done so at Under-16, Under-17 and Under-19 levels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/england/all-teams/players?p=355383 |title=Profile |work=The Football Association |accessdate=13 March 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Iltaf Ahmed]] {{spaced ndash}} British Pakistani footballer who was the number one goalkeeper of [[Pakistan national football team]]<ref>{{FIFA player|288767|Ahmed Iltaf}}</ref>\n* [[Hamza Choudhury]] \u2013 British footballer of Bangladeshi and Afro-Caribbean origin\n* [[Kashif Siddiqi]] {{spaced ndash}} English-born Pakistani [[association football|footballer]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chelseafc.com/page/LatestNews/0,,10268~2718608,00.html|title=MALOUDA LAUNCHES FOURTH ASIAN STAR APPEAL|date=3 April 2012|publisher=Chelsea F.C.}}</ref>\n* [[Omar Kader]] \u2013 Scottish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Arbroath F.C.|Arbroath]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Robertson|first1=Neil|title=Arbroath boss Dick Campbell in quadruple signing swoop|url=https://www.thecourier.co.uk/fp/sport/football/scottish-league-2/170139/arbroath-boss-dick-campbell-quadruple-signing-swoop/|accessdate=11 May 2