rist\n* [[Hasib Hussain]] \u2013 [[7 July 2005 London bombings|7/7]] bomber<ref name=\"7 July\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/4676861.stm|title=London bombers: Key facts|work=BBC News|date=21 July 2005|accessdate=29 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Jihadi John]], ISIS terrorist\n*[[Junaid Hussain]], ISIS terrorist\n* [[Mohammad Sidique Khan]] \u2013 oldest of the four [[Homegrown terrorism|homegrown]] suicide bombers and believed to be the leader responsible for the [[7 July 2005 London bombings]]<ref name=\"7 July\"/>\n* [[Abu Bakr Mansha]] \u2013 convicted under the [[Terrorism Act 2000]]<ref name=\"convicted\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/4553150.stm|work=BBC News|title=Man convicted under Terrorism Act|date=22 December 2005|accessdate=2006-10-12}}</ref>\n* [[Bethnal Green trio|Shamima Begum and Kadiza Sultana]] \u2013 Two of the three British schoolgirls from [[Bethnal Green Academy]] who left home in February 2015 to join the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]].<ref name=\"bbcbegumsultana\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-31568241|title='Syria-bound' London girls: Please come home, families plead|work=[[BBC News]]|date=21 February 2015|accessdate=1 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Sharmeena Begum]] \u2013 British schoolgirl from Bethnal Green Academy who left home in December 2014 to join the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant.<ref name=\"theguardianbegum\">{{cite news |last=Dodd|first=Vikram|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/13/sharmeena-begum-first-of-british-girl-isis|title=Sharmeena Begum \u2013 British girl left to join Isis after upheavals at home|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=13 March 2015|accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"independentsharmeena\">{{cite news |last=Buchanan|first=Rose Troup|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/sharmeena-begum-fourth-isis-schoolgirl-named-as-father-claims-he-told-police-to-warn-families-10108507.html|title=Missing schoolgirls: First teenager who fled from ea