ol of Agriculture, Policy and Development at the [[University of Reading]]<ref name=eco>[http://ca.ecoport.org/bioamir.html?height=500&width=620 Amir Kassam OBE, FIBiol, CBiol, PhD, MS, BSc (Hons).] Ecoport Conservation Agriculture. Retrieved 4 July 2017.</ref>\n* [[Ash Amin]] {{spaced ndash}} Head of Geography at [[Cambridge University]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.geog.cam.ac.uk/people/amin/|title=Professor Ash Amin PhD |website= |publisher=University of Cambridge |accessdate=15 August 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Tipu Aziz|Tipu Zahed Aziz]] {{spaced ndash}} professor of [[neurosurgery]] at the [[John Radcliffe Hospital]] in Oxford; lecturer at [[Magdalen College, Oxford]] and [[Imperial College London]] medical school<ref name=\"oxfordprivatehealth\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.oxfordprivatehealth.co.uk/consultants/consultants.asp?consultantid=452|title=Prof. Tipu Aziz |work= |location= |accessdate= }}</ref>\n* [[Azim Surani]] \u2013 developmental biologist who has been Marshall\u2013Walton Professor at the [[Wellcome Trust]]/[[Cancer Research UK]] [[Gurdon Institute]] at the [[University of Cambridge]] since 1992, and Director of Germline and Epigenomics Research since 2013.<ref name=scopus>{{Scopus id}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gurdon.cam.ac.uk/research/surani|title=Azim Surani \u2014 The Gurdon Institute|website=Gurdon.cam.ac.uk|accessdate=29 August 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Azra Meadows]] OBE {{spaced ndash}} honorary lecturer in the Institute of Biomedical and Life Sciences at The [[University of Glasgow]]<ref name=queen>{{cite web|accessdate=21 February 2012 |title=Queen honours ZSL Council Members |date=14 June 2008 |publisher=ZSL.com |url=http://www.zsl.org/science/news/queen-honours-zsls-secretary,478,NS.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104205422/http://www.zsl.org/science/news/queen-honours-zsls-secretary%2C478%2CNS.html |archivedate= 4 January 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Delwar Hussain]] \u2013 writer, anthropologist and correspondent for ''[[The Guardian]]''. In 2013, his first book ''Boundaries Undermined: The Ruins of Progress on the Bangladesh-India Border'' was published.<ref name=\"spitalfieldslifehussain\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.spitalfieldslife.com/2013/07/22/delwar-hussain-writer-anthropologist/|title=Delwar Hussain, Writer & Anthropologist|work= |location= |publisher=Spitalfields Life|date=22 July 2013|accessdate=1 August 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Dilwar Hussain]] {{spaced ndash}} research fellow at [[The Islamic Foundation]] in Leicester; co-authored the 2004 book ''British Muslims Between Assimilation and Segregation''; is on the Home Office's committee tackling radicalisation and extremism<ref name=\"independenthussain\">{{cite news |last=Hussain|first=Dilwar|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/commentators/dilwar-hussain-never-mind-what-we-are-against-what-are-we-for-308565.html|title=Dilwar Hussain: Never mind what we are against. What are we for?|location= London|newspaper=The Independent|date=28 August 2005|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Alfred Neville May|Dr Muhammad Haroon (Alfred Neville May)]]\n* [[Ehsan Masood]] {{spaced ndash}} science writer, journalist and broadcaster; editor of ''[[Research Fortnight]]'' and ''Research Europe'';<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.researchresearch.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=17&Itemid=17|title=Research Europe|website=Research Professional|access-date=6 August 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130904003114/http://www.researchresearch.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=17&Itemid=17|archive-date=4 September 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> teaches International Science Policy at [[Imperial College London]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.researchresearch.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=12&Itemid=12|title=Total Funding Awareness|website=Research Professional|access-date=6 August 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130614083909/http://www.