ford-based entrepreneur; owns a specialist car design company; broke records in 2008 for paying \u00a3440,000 for a distinctive \"F1\" number plate;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/driving/news/article3252162.ece |title=Record \u00a3440,000 paid for F1 number plate |author=Andrew Norfolk |date= 25 January 2008|work= |publisher=Times Newspapers Ltd |accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref> previously showed an interest in purchasing [[Newcastle F.C.|Newcastle football club]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/newcastle-united/3725482/Newcastle-United-targeted-by-multi-millionaire-entrepreneur-Afzal-Kahn.html |title=Newcastle United targeted by multi-millionaire entrepreneur Afzal Kahn |author=Rob Stewart |date= 12 December 2008|work= |publisher=Telegraph Media Group |accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n* [[Aktar Islam]] {{spaced ndash}} restaurateur, curry chef and businessman; in 2010, his restaurant Lasan won the Best Local Restaurant category on Channel 4's ''[[The F Word (TV series)|The F Word]]'';<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/west_midlands/8447841.stm|title=Birmingham restaurant Lasan wins Ramsay's 'F Word'|work=[[BBC News]]|date=8 January 2010|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref> in 2011, Islam won the Central regional heat to reach the final of the BBC Two series ''[[Great British Menu]]''<ref name=\"theasiantodayislam\">{{cite news|url=http://www.theasiantoday.com/article.aspx?articleId=2455|title=Aktar Islam: Kicking it with the Big Boys!|work=[[The Asian Today]]|date=16 June 2011|accessdate=1 July 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029192215/http://www.theasiantoday.com/article.aspx?articleId=2455|archivedate=29 October 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"rewiredpr\">{{cite news|url=http://rewiredpr.com/news/chef_aktar_islam_to_feature_in_this_years_bbc_two_series_great_british_menu/|title=Chef Aktar Islam to feature in this year'