ure.html?docId=1000212993 |title=Confessions of a Fake Sheikh |author=Harper Collins |publisher=[[News Corporation (1980\u20132013)|News Corporation]] |accessdate=18 July 2011 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120720132431/http://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/feature.html?docId=1000212993 |archive-date=20 July 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> the ''[[News of the World]]'' paid his six-figure salary, plus an editorial and technical support budget <ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/personal-view/3592327/The-dirty-digger.html |title=The dirty digger |author=Telegraph News & Media Group |date= 8 June 2003|work= The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n* [[Mehdi Hasan]] {{spaced ndash}} senior politics editor at the ''New Statesman'' and a former news and current affairs editor at Channel 4<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/blogs/mehdi-hasan/2011/01/pakistan-muslims-taseer-west |title=Pakistan Muslims Taseer-West |author=Mehdi Hassan |work= [[New Statesman]] |accessdate=15 July 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Miqdaad Versi]]{{spaced ndash}}assistant secretary general of the Muslim Council of Britain, media commentator, and advocate for accurate reporting on Muslims.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-38655760|title=The man correcting stories about Muslims|last=Nye|first=Catrin|date=2017-01-19|newspaper=BBC News|access-date=2017-02-17|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/miqdaad-versi|title=Miqdaad Versi|website=the Guardian|access-date=2017-02-17}}</ref>\n* [[Mishal Husain]] {{spaced ndash}} anchor for [[BBC World]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/tv_and_radio/article6870956.ece |title=Significant others |author=Alexia Skinitis |date= 17 October 2009|work= |publisher=Times Newspapers |accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n*  [[Muhammad Abdul Bari]]{{spaced ndash}} Chairman of the [[East London Mo