e, Jonathan |authorlink=Jonathan R\u00e9e |title=Send in the Idiots, by Kamran Nazeer |work=The Independent |date=24 August 2006 |url=http://enjoyment.independent.co.uk/books/reviews/article359017.ece |location=London |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070410213753/http://enjoyment.independent.co.uk/books/reviews/article359017.ece |archivedate=10 April 2007 }}</ref>\n* [[Ghulam Murshid]] \u2013 author, scholar and journalist; numerous  literary awards from India and Bangladesh, including the [[Bangla Academy]] award<ref name=\"openlibrary\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=https://openlibrary.org/a/OL520257A/Ghulam_Murshid|title=Ghulam Murshid|work= |location= |publisher=Open Library|accessdate=10 March 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Idris Khan]] \u2013 artist based in London<ref name=Miro>[http://www.victoria-miro.com/artists/35,biog/ Biography], Victoria Miro Gallery</ref>\n* [[Imtiaz Dharker]] \u2013 poet and documentary filmmaker<ref>{{cite web |url=http://anthology.aqa.org.uk/index.asp?currmenu=dharker |title=Digital Anthology |author=AQA |accessdate=15 July 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327205627/http://anthology.aqa.org.uk/index.asp?currmenu=dharker |archive-date=27 March 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Kaniz Ali]] \u2013 makeup artist and freelance beauty columnist;<ref name=\"shoutarabia\" /> won the \"Best Make-Up Artist\" category at the 2011 International Asian Fashion Awards<ref name=\"pukkapr\"/>\n* [[Kia Abdullah]] \u2013 novelist and journalist; contributes to ''[[The Guardian]]'' newspaper<ref name=\"Guardianprofile\">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/kiaabdullah|title=Kia Abdullah|location=London|work=The Guardian|date=4 July 2008|accessdate=2 February 2009}}</ref> and has written two novels\n* [[Mohsin Hamid]] \u2013 Pakistani writer; novels ''[[Moth Smoke]]'' (2000), ''[[The Reluctant Fundamentalist]]'' (2007), and ''How to Get Filthy Rich in Rising Asia'' (2013)<ref>[https://ww