on]], former Labour MP for Tooting and former [[Shadow Secretary of State for Justice]] and [[Shadow Lord Chancellor]]<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite news| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-11499638 |work=BBC News |title=Ex-Home Secretary Johnson is named shadow chancellor | date=8 October 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Saqib Bhatti]] - Conservative MP for [[Meriden (UK Parliament constituency)|Meriden]], first elected in the [[2019 United Kingdom general election]].<ref name=\"birminghammail\">{{cite web|url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/midlands-news/general-election-2019-meriden-results-17396845|author=James Rodger|title=Meriden general election results 2019 - Birmingham Live|website=birminghammail.co.uk|accessdate=2019-12-13}}</ref>\n* [[Shahid Malik]] {{spaced ndash}} former Labour MP for Dewsbury;  Minister for International Development in Gordon Brown's government<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/terrorism-in-the-uk/7498615/Chaplains-can-help-fight-against-Muslim-extremism-says-Shahid-Malik.html|title=Chaplains can help fight against Muslim extremism, says Shahid Malik |author=Religious Affairs Correspondent |date= 23 March 2010|work= |publisher=Telegraph Media Group |accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n* [[Shabana Mahmood]] {{spaced ndash}} Labour MP For [[Birmingham Ladywood]]\n* [[Tahir Ali]] - MP representing [[Birmingham Hall Green]] for the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/politics/constituencies/E14000562|title=Birmingham Hall Green parliamentary constituency - Election 2019|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref>\n* [[Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh]] {{spaced ndash}} former SNP MP for [[Ochil and South Perthshire (UK Parliament constituency)|Ochil and South Perthshire]]\n* [[Tulip Siddiq]] {{spaced ndash}} Labour MP for [[Hampstead and Kilburn (UK Parliament constituency)|Hampstead and Kilburn constituency]]\n* [[Yasmin Qureshi]] {{spaced ndash}} Labour MP for [[Bolton South East]]\n* [