our-corbyn-may |title=Almost 4,000 people may have been denied vote by election ID pilots |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2018-05-03 |accessdate=2018-05-04}}</ref>\n* [[Sadiq Khan]] \u2013 elected [[Mayor of London]] in May 2016\n\n===Other===\n* [[Mushtaq Ahmad (Lord Lieutenant)|Mushtaq Ahmad]] \u2013 [[Lord Lieutenant of Lanarkshire]]. He was the first [[Asian people|Asian]] to serve as [[Provost (civil)|Provost]] of a [[Subdivisions of Scotland|Scottish council]]<ref name=\"dailyrecord.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/local-news/mushtaq-ahmad-succeed-gilbert-cox-2828948|title=Mushtaq Ahmad to succeed Gilbert Cox as lord lieutenant of Lanarkshire|first=Judith|last=Tonner|date=1 December 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"dailyrecord.co.uk\"/>\n* [[Shahnaz Ali]] \u2013  British [[Muslim]] woman  known for her leadership role in equality, inclusion and human rights in the [[National Health Service]] and local government in England<ref>The Guardian: Five minutes with \u2026 an NHS director for equality and inclusion https://www.theguardian.com/healthcare-network/2013/feb/01/nhs-director-equality-inclusion</ref>\n* [[Bashir Maan]] \u2013 Pakistani-Scottish politician, businessman and writer<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.muslimnews.co.uk/awards/index.php?page=2002/maan |title=Awards for Excellence |work=The Muslim News |accessdate=15 July 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825212407/http://www.muslimnews.co.uk/awards/index.php?page=2002%2Fmaan |archivedate=25 August 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n* [[Munira Mirza]] \u2013 was the Deputy Mayor for Education and Culture of London. Born in Oldham.<ref>{{cite web|title=Munira Mirza|url=http://www.london.gov.uk/who-runs-london/mayor/mayoral-team/munira-mirza|work=Mayor of London: Mayoral Team|publisher=Greater London Authority|accessdate=16 July 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120719005232/http://www.london.gov.uk/who-runs-london/mayor/mayoral-team/munira