ellow]] of the [[Royal Pharmaceutical Society]]; an honour bestowed to those who have achieved excellence and distinction in their pharmacy career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.rpharms.com/uncategorized/2016/07/01/congratulations-to-nadia-bukhari-on-her-achievements-as-the-youngest-female-asian-fellow/|title=Congratulations to Nadia Bukhari - Women in Pharmacy - RPS|date=1 July 2016|website=Blog.rpharms.com|accessdate=10 August 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Qanta Ahmed]] \u2013 physician specializing in [[sleep disorders]]. She is also an author and a [[newspaper columnist]]<ref name=\"winthrop\">{{Citation | url = http://www.winthrop.org/departments/specialtycenters/sleep-disorders-center/sleep-disorder-center-team.cfm?qanta-ahmed | title = Sleep Medicine Specialist | publisher = Winthrop University Hospital | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110911043807/http://www.winthrop.org/departments/specialtycenters/sleep-disorders-center/sleep-disorder-center-team.cfm?qanta-ahmed | archivedate = 2011-09-11 }}.</ref>\n* [[Rozina Ali]] {{spaced ndash}} [[Microsurgery|microvascular]] [[Reconstructive surgery|reconstructive]] [[Plastic surgery|plastic]] [[surgeon]] and [[Consultant (medicine)|consultant]] with a specialist interest in [[breast reconstruction]]; television presenter<ref name=\"eveningnews24\">{{cite news|last=Bale|first=David|url=http://www.eveningnews24.co.uk/news/norwich_plastic_surgeon_rozina_ali_a_happy_person_will_always_look_good_1_1486551l|title=Norwich plastic surgeon Rozina Ali: 'A happy person will always look good'|location=Norwich|work=[[Norwich Evening News]]|date=20 August 2013|accessdate=1 February 2013}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* [[Sheraz Daya]] {{spaced ndash}} [[ophthalmologist]] and eye surgeon, best known for his founding of the Centre for Sight in 1996 and use of stem-cell research during sight recovery surgery<ref name=White>{{cite web |url=http://www.opticianonline.net/Articles/Article.aspx?liArticleID=17694&PrinterFriendly=true |author=Emma White |title=Feature: Center for Sight |accessdate=6 March 2013 |publisher=Optician Online |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203021737/http://www.opticianonline.net/Articles/Article.aspx?liArticleID=17694&PrinterFriendly=true |archive-date=3 December 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.centreforsight.com/about-us/who-are-we/surgeons/sheraz-daya |date=10 November 2012 |accessdate=29 April 2013 |title=Sheraz Daya}}</ref>\n* [[Tipu Aziz|Tipu Zahed Aziz]] {{spaced ndash}} Professor of [[neurosurgery]] at the [[John Radcliffe Hospital]] in Oxford; lecturer at [[Magdalen College, Oxford]] and [[Imperial College London]] medical school<ref name=\"oxfordprivatehealth\"/>\n* [[Alimuddin Zumla]] {{spaced ndash}} Director of infectious diseases, University College Hospital, London\n\n==Sport==\n===Boxing===\n* [[Adil Anwar]] {{spaced ndash}} British light-welterweight boxer and multiple title winner<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adilanwar.co.uk/home.php |title=The Platinum Kid |author=Adil Anwar |publisher=Lemon Web Service |accessdate=15 July 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100128211153/http://www.adilanwar.co.uk/home.php |archivedate=28 January 2010 }}</ref>\n* [[Adnan Amar]] {{spaced ndash}} British light-middleweight boxer, multiple title winner<ref>[http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?human_id=48911&cat=boxer \"Adnan Amar\"], BoxRec.</ref>  \n* [[Amer Khan]] {{spaced ndash}} former undefeated light-heavyweight boxer, Central Area championship winner\n* [[Amir Khan (British boxer)|Amir Khan]] {{spaced ndash}} British light-welterweight Boxer, 2004 Olympics silver medalist, and former world champion\n* [[Haroon Khan]] {{spaced ndash}} super-flyweight boxer and commonwealth bronze medalist<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/general/athletics/khan-wins-bronze-madal-for-pakistan-2103808.html |tit