han|work=ESPNcricinfo|accessdate=1 December 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Aamir Farooque]] \u2013 former Pakistani-born English cricketer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/9/9114/Minor_Counties_Championship_Matches.html|title=The Home of CricketArchive|website=www.cricketarchive.com}}</ref>\n* [[Adil Rashid]] \u2013 English cricketer who plays for [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire]] and England Under-19s<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2011/apr/10/adil-rashid-yorkshire-worcestershire|title=Yorkshire's Adil Rashid pivotal in victory against Worcestershire |author=David Hopps |date= 10 April 2011|work= The Guardian |accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n* [[Ajaz Akhtar]] \u2013 former Pakistani people-born English [[cricket]]er<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/7/7286/Minor_Counties_Trophy_Matches.html|title=The Home of CricketArchive|website=www.cricketarchive.com}}</ref>\n* [[Ajmal Shahzad]] \u2013 cricketer who plays for [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club]] and represents England in all three formats of the game<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/player/21431.html |title=Ajmal Shahzad|website= |publisher=ESPN EMEA |accessdate=15 July 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Akbar Ansari]] {{spaced ndash}} English first-class and List A cricketer who played his First-class games for [[Cambridge University Cricket Club]] and Cambridge University Centre of Cricketing Excellence,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Players/90/90841/f_Batting_by_Team.html | title=First-class Batting and Fielding For Each Team by Akbar Ansari|date=15 August 2008 |publisher=Cricket archive}}</ref> and List A cricket for [[Marylebone Cricket Club]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Players/90/90841/a_Batting_by_Team.html | title=ListA Batting and Fielding For Each Team by Akbar Ansari|date=15 August 2008 | publisher=Cricket archive}}</ref>\n* [[Alamgir S