}} [[Somalia|Somali]]-born British middle distance athlete specialising in the [[800 metres]]<ref>[http://www.thepowerof10.info/athletes/profile.aspx?athleteid=47405 \"Mukhtar Mohammed\"], Power of 10.</ref>\n* [[Shokat Ali]]{{spaced ndash}} English [[snooker]] player of [[Pakistani people|Pakistani]] descent; represents Pakistan in international tournaments\n* [[Zia Mahmood]] {{spaced ndash}}Pakistani professional [[Contract bridge|bridge]] player; [[World Bridge Federation]] and [[American Contract Bridge League]] Grand Life Master<ref>[http://www.worldbridge.org/departments/mps/mastersinfo.asp?qcat=O Open World Grand Masters] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130719015847/http://www.worldbridge.org/departments/mps/mastersinfo.asp?qcat=O |date=19 July 2013 }} table. World Bridge Federation.</ref>\n* [[Hammad Miah]] {{spaced ndash}} British snooker player{{citation needed|date=January 2019}}\n* [[Zubair Hoque]] {{spaced ndash}} British single-seat racecar driver{{citation needed|date=January 2019}}\n\n==Militants==\n* [[Abdel-Majed Abdel Bary]], ISIS terrorist\n* [[Hasib Hussain]] \u2013 [[7 July 2005 London bombings|7/7]] bomber<ref name=\"7 July\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/4676861.stm|title=London bombers: Key facts|work=BBC News|date=21 July 2005|accessdate=29 June 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Jihadi John]], ISIS terrorist\n*[[Junaid Hussain]], ISIS terrorist\n* [[Mohammad Sidique Khan]] \u2013 oldest of the four [[Homegrown terrorism|homegrown]] suicide bombers and believed to be the leader responsible for the [[7 July 2005 London bombings]]<ref name=\"7 July\"/>\n* [[Abu Bakr Mansha]] \u2013 convicted under the [[Terrorism Act 2000]]<ref name=\"convicted\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/4553150.stm|work=BBC News|title=Man convicted under Terrorism Act|date=22 December 2005|accessdate=2006-10-12}}</ref>\n* [[Bethnal Green trio|Shamima Begum and Kadiza Sultana]] \u2013 Two of the three British schoolgirls from [[Bethnal Green Academy]] who left home in February 2015 to join the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]].<ref name=\"bbcbegumsultana\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-31568241|title='Syria-bound' London girls: Please come home, families plead|work=[[BBC News]]|date=21 February 2015|accessdate=1 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Sharmeena Begum]] \u2013 British schoolgirl from Bethnal Green Academy who left home in December 2014 to join the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant.<ref name=\"theguardianbegum\">{{cite news |last=Dodd|first=Vikram|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/13/sharmeena-begum-first-of-british-girl-isis|title=Sharmeena Begum \u2013 British girl left to join Isis after upheavals at home|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=13 March 2015|accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"independentsharmeena\">{{cite news |last=Buchanan|first=Rose Troup|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/sharmeena-begum-fourth-isis-schoolgirl-named-as-father-claims-he-told-police-to-warn-families-10108507.html|title=Missing schoolgirls: First teenager who fled from east London named as Sharmeena Begum as father says he told police to warn trio's families|work=[[The Independent]]|date=14 March 2015|accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Shehzad Tanweer]] \u2013 [[7 July 2005 London bombings|7/7]] bomber<ref name=\"7 July\"/>\n*[[Usman Khan (terrorist)|Usman Khan]], London knife attacker\n\n==Other==\n* [[Amal Azzudin]] \u2013 Scottish human rights activist\n* [[Basil Al Bayati]] {{spaced ndash}} architect, designer and writer; leading proponent of the school of [[Metaphoric Architecture]]\n* [[Asif Ahmad]] {{spaced ndash}} [[Her Majesty's Diplomatic Service|British diplomat]], serving as the British Ambassador to the Republic of the Philippines\n* Dr [[Humayra Abedin]] {{spaced ndash}} [[National Health Service (England)|National Health Service]] doctor of medicine who became a [[cause c\u00e9l\u00e8bre]] after her parents tried to force her into marriage and held her captive until  freed by court order in 2008<ref name=\"timesonlineabedin\">{{cite news |last= Bremner|first= Charles|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/uk/crime/article5340058.ece|title='Forced marriage' doctor, Humayra Abedin, freed by Bangladesh court|location= London|work=BBC News|date=15 December 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"bbcnewsabedin\">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/7782182.stm|title=Captive doctor to return to UK|work=[[BBC News]]|date=15 December 2008}}</ref>\n* [[Hussain Bisad]] {{spaced ndash}} one of the tallest men in the world, at {{height | m=2.32}}<ref name=bio>\n{{cite news\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/1847666.stm\n|title=Second tallest man has biggest hands\n|publisher=[[BBC News website]]\n|date=28 February 2002\n|accessdate=13 October 2008}}\n</ref>  \n* [[Robina Qureshi]] {{spaced ndash}} Scottish human rights campaigner<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/the-estate-where-asylum-seekers-abandon-hope-1918347.html |title=The estate where asylum seekers abandon hope |date= 9 March 2010|work= The Independent |accessdate=15 July 2011 |location=London}}</ref>\n* [[Ruhal Ahmed]] {{spaced ndash}} former [[Guantanamo Bay detention camp|Guantanamo Bay]] detainee depicted in the film ''[[The Road to Guantanamo]]''<ref name=\"washingtonpost\">{{cite news |last=Dodds|first=Paisley|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/06/12/AR2006061200235.html|title=AP: Gitmo Movie Subjects Discuss Suicide|location= |work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=12 June 2006|accessdate=15 February 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"independentruhal\">{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/guantanamo-britons-left-in-limbo-as-talks-with-us-stall-570881.html|title=Guantanamo Britons left in limbo as talks with US stall|location= London|newspaper=The Independent|date=22 February 2004|accessdate=15 February 2009}}</ref>\n* [[Saiman Miah]] {{spaced ndash}} architecture student who designed the \u00a35 coins for the [[2012 Summer Olympics|2012 London Summer Olympics]]<ref name=\"bbcsaimanmiah\">{{cite news |last=Shama|first=Saveem|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-15718464|title=London 2012 \u00a35 coin design success for Midlands pair|location= London|work=BBC News|date=14 November 2011|accessdate=31 May 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"thedailystar\">{{cite news |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/suppliments/2012/anniversary_2012/section3/sports02.htm|title=21 Anniversary Supplement|location= London|work=[[BBC News]]|date=23 May 2010|accessdate=31 May 2012}}</ref>\n* Hans Ramzan {{spaced ndash}} won design of the year for inventing a HIV detector <ref>{{cite news |url=https://designmuseum.org/exhibitions/past-exhibitions/beazley-designs-of-the-year-2018/qa-with-hans-ramzan?utm_source=instagram&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=catch_ig |title=Q&A with Hans Ramzan |author=The Design Museum, London |date= 11 September 2019|work= |publisher=Design Museum |accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Sahil Saeed]] {{spaced ndash}} boy kidnapped in Pakistan in 2010; released unharmed after the payment of a ransom<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/8575435.stm |title=Kidnapped boy Sahil Saeed returns to the UK |author=BBC News |date= 18 March 2010|work= |publisher=BBC |accessdate=15 July 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Shabina Begum]] {{spaced ndash}} was involved in the leading [[House of Lords]] case UKHL 15 ''R (Begum) v Governors of Denbigh High School'' (2006)<ref>[http://www.bailii.org/uk/cases/UKHL/2006/15.html UKHL 15 ''R (Begum) v Governors of Denbigh High School'' (2006)]</ref> on the legal regulation of religious symbols and dress under the [[Human Rights Act 1998]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[Islam in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Islam in England]]\n*[[Islam in Northern Ireland]]\n*[[Islam in Scotland]]\n*[[Islam in Wales]]\n*[[Religion in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[List of American Muslims]]\n*[[List of Canadian Muslims]]\n{{Portal|Islam|United Kingdom}}